# Backend Rules — NestJS + Prisma

## Module structure
- One NestJS module per domain (scenarios, metrics, logger)
- Services are injectable and exported — controllers are never exported
- Never put business logic in controllers — controllers only validate input and call service
- DTOs for all request bodies using class-validator decorators

## NestJS conventions
- All services: inject Logger via constructor, never instantiate directly
- Use @Injectable(), @Controller(), @Get(), @Post() — never express req/res directly
- Error handling: throw HttpException or built-in NestJS exceptions, never return error objects
- Add @ApiTags() and @ApiOperation() to every controller for Swagger

## Prisma
- All models: PascalCase names, camelCase fields
- Always use cuid() for IDs — never uuid() or autoincrement
- Never query Prisma directly from controllers — always via service
- Run `npx prisma migrate dev` after any schema change, never `db push` in dev

## TypeScript
- Strict mode enabled — no `any` types
- All async functions return typed Promises
- Interfaces for all shared types, not inline object types

## Observability — enforced on every scenario run
Every call to scenario.service.ts runScenario() MUST:
1. Call metricsService.increment(type, status)
2. Call this.logger.log/warn/error with structured JSON payload
3. Call prisma.scenarioRun.create() to persist the record
4. If type === system_error: call Sentry.captureException(error)
